<br>
[side bar] Why is it that melees think that a damage shield cast on them is damage THEY are doing? <br>
<br>
The only time people know when a wizard has done damage with crits. Then it's jaw dropping, OMG. If you sit out a round, then it's comments of &quot;this mob is much harder&quot; which always makes me laugh. <br>
<br>
I encourage all wizards and mages to send feedback to Sony saying we want all our Damage to show up, just like does for melees. They don't even have to add a second line, it can be added to the line that shows when it says &quot;A Moss snakes skin is ripped by shards of ice and wind for 1120 non melee damage)<br>
<br>
If people can SEE what we are doing, they will change thier minds about how good a wizard is.<br>
<br>
Thankfully, I have a good group of friends, and always have someone to play with. In my group is another wizard. We like to tag team ice comet and other spells. I have a hotkey set up that sends him a tell pauses for 4 seconds, then casts ice comet. Often they hit at the same time. When you do 45% of a mobs Hitpoints in the blink of an eye, people notice. <br>
<br>
