<br>
However, lots of wizards are not nearly that level, and other classes don't have those advantages.  The need for very fast mana refill effect is still there, especially considering all a melee has to do is find one of 3 healing classes to refill their HP bar nearly instantly, and they can get AA first aid, and AA regen to help when they are experiancing downtime on their own--not great, but it's there.<br>
<br>
What Is needed to make wizards, or any caster class, wanted in groups is group utility spells. Priests Heal and buff, Chanters have Slow/haste, Clarity, and Mez.  Mages hurt nearly as bad as we do, and Necromancers are Grouping lepers till they get the group taps, and even then aren't real desired, it's about average then.<br>
<br>
For Wizards, I'd suggest DPS enhancing spells like Reverse a Reverse Damage sheild.  I'd also suggest a mana regen spell that refills a mana bar in 30-45 seconds, but ends if the recipient stands up or is aggroed.  Even if that effect is not given to wizards, it should go to someone other than enchanters as they are the only real source of mana other than a bard currently, and all core grouping roles should be redundant in at least 3 classes due to the number of classes vs. the number of group slots. <p><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=448514">Antrygus Windrose </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lornick65>Lornick65</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 9:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> balance</span><hr size=1> The major concern is obviously more groupablity for wizards.  Allowing everyone to see your spell damage would likely have people just filter it off after 5 minutes.  Bane spells are a cool idea.  I don't think it really adds to the groupability of a wizard.  But it's a cool idea.  I think a number of the spells suggested so far offer more groupablity really.<br>
<br>
Utter Concentration-- Buff that locks the recipient in place, and causes all spells to be un-interuptible for the duration.<br>
<br>
Know Allies-- Spell that gives a list of the targets positive factions. A second spell in this line might provide all negative faction hits provided by the mob. Usefull for knowing before you kill a mob what hits you will take. A third variety might provide all mobs or factions the target will assist in battle<br>
<br>
Temporal Stasis-- Freezes a target in time for 30 seconds, making it unable to move, attack, and makes it invunerable for the duration. (suggest make the refresh 25 sec or so that a wizard can only maintain one mob frozen in time)<br>
<br>
Portal Lock-- The target of this spell will find any attempts to cast gate/port spells collapse.<br>
<br>
Lava Walk-- Allows the target to walk upon lava as if it were solid ground<br>
<br>
These are the kind of original spells that will help wizards be more groupable.  I also think wizards should get a spell that sends target to bind point.  Why this ability was given to bards and not wizards is beyond me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/28/03 9:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells</span><hr size=1> If we did get some better mana spells, I would seriously want them to be self only. One easy idea is drop the Harverst spell line down in levels and add another one. Make it a Harvest over Time spell. Somewhere inbetween harverst and Clarity. It doesn't increase mana all at once like Harvest does, but spreads it out over several ticks. Maybe like 20 mana each tick, for a total of 500 mana. Same cast and recast as a normal harvest. Only your not stunned, you can move about as normal and cast. You also can't cast other Harvest spells while it is working. If you try, you get the, This spell would not take hold on you, and you have to wait to recast it.<br>
