<br>
However, a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>group</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> harvest would be fine, only I could easily see Sony making everyone that benifits from it get stunned.  <br>
<br>
For me, it seems a spell that gives us 50% -100% of our mana back in 30-40 seconds seems to unbalance things. Even though I'm a wizard, and I fully support better wizards, this would make wizards non stop nuking machines, which really doesn't seem fair to any other class that uses nukes or dots or whatever. <br>
<br>
A group harvest would be a boon to all casters, clerics to. If it gives back, say 300 or 400 mana, that's enough for a nuke from you or heals from a cleric. <br>
<br>
The harvest over time would be to shorten you down time, not remove down time. So yes, my idea does address the down time issue with wizards. Removing any down time for a wizard, even after level 60 id unbalancing. Yes, enchanters can steal mana from mobs that have it. Yes mages can cast and reclaim more mana with pets (they still have to take the time to do it). Personally, that is the spell that needs to be nerfed, if simply for the fact that the idea of getting more mana back then it cost to creat something just seems wrong. <br>
<br>
Hell, even if you cast it after the first nuke, it would still be helpful. 20 or 30 mana a tick, at say level 60, with a horse, and flowing thought would really fill up the mana quick. Since I believe 15 is the best you can get with flowing thought, I could be mistaken.<br>
<br>
As for stuff that would make a wizard more group friendly? Well, how about a group form of O'kiels Radiation? Which is stackable with other DS. On top of that, it gives FR. They should also extend the O'Kiels into a cold based and magic based lines, which are not stackable with each other. <br>
<br>
Or how about a familiar that acts as a group buff? Say the level 60 familar gives anyone grouped with the wizard, see invis, increase all resists by 10, and gives them a 2 mana regen per tick. <br>
<br>
Yes, traditionally, wizards are a selfish class when it comes to sharing benifical magic. We've focused more on offensive and destructive magic rather then helpful magic. So offering more buffs to other people seems out of line, but extending sefl buffs into group buffs would be in line I feel. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lornick65>Lornick65</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 10:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells</span><hr size=1> I think the focus needs to be kept not on what you can do that will help the other players, but on what only you can do to npc's that will benefit the group.  Wizard has never been a support class.  imo they never should be.  There are plenty of other ways to improve group desireablity.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 325<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 4:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells</span><hr size=1> O'Keils may stack with other DS's, which is cool, and the line should be modified for the earlier spells, and continued foward... but it does not stack with some buff that everyone wants from rangers(?), not sure what it is, but I get yelled at in groups for using it.<br>
