<br>
Nothing you said changes or refutes a single thing I said in my last post.  I agree, many wizards don't want a buff, but untill we do get some kind of group friendly utility that helps the group, we will remain as we are, unless we suddenly do 2x the damage anyone else is doing. <p><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=448514">Antrygus Windrose </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=utnayrduscratu>Utnayr Duscratu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/03 3:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells</span><hr size=1> Personally, I'm in favor of just displaying our damage right along with the melee damage.  Anyone that has their melee damage on doesn't care much about the spam, and when they see their hits, and then they see that 1.2k or higher hitting consistantly from us, then we will see people looking at us more outside the zone of crits, and that's a good thing.  Even if they only saw the draught lines from the 50's, they'd see the numbers and their minds would be registering that we did that.  This is the best idea for a solution imho.<br>
<br>
I have heard some good ideas for spells, but I have to agree with the people that say that we need to have more group desirability without making us solo any better.<br>
<br>
For this reason, I have to stand behind the weapon buff ideas.  A little different than a proc in that it doesn't make a check to work, but it does much less damage per hit.  Even 5 to 10 damage per hit on every melee in the group would be noticable in most situations, and pretty much everytime that's less than would be done by the damage shields that mages excel so well at.<br>
<br>
Making O'Kiels stackable would not do much, unless it was the new one.  I wouldn't mind being able to cast it on others, or have two other series similar to O'Kiels that covered cold and magic (maybe the cold one giving EB instead of lev or something, for example), the result would be a little more utility with interesting, multi-result spells.  I think single target versions should be added before an all out group version, but that's just in keeping with the concept of mastering a spell before getting a better version of it.  I really like this idea, since O'Kiels is finally somewhat useful, and this would open us up just a little, which in my opinion is all we really need.<br>
<br>
Damage debuffs are not a bad idea either.  They would help with those mobs that do cast, and therefore at least give us some areas where we are more group desirable, even though most damage is melee.<br>
<br>
Baron Utnayr Duscratu-Ce`Moerr<br>
Wizard of the 56th Pillar of Sol Ro's Fury<br>
Slave to Shekkra Ce`Moerr<br>
