<br>
It's not so much that wizards don't offer anything to a group, it's that people that have no understanding of wizards or have never played one to high up can't see what a wizard offers. Mezzes and hastes and slows and heals are all directly tangiable to most people in a group. <br>
<br>
Wizards damage isn't dirctly noticable. But wizards can shorten any fight considerablly. And if someone can't see that, then the problem lies on thier end. Anyone I've grouped with over and over again soon realize this, once I'm not with them. Wizards = more damage = mobs dead faster = less healing from cleric = less down time for cleric = more playing. That is a long equations and many people won't aggree with it. Someone will say, but after taking down one mob, I'm OOM. Well, at level 51, I have 2800 mana. That's 13 Daughts of Fire, which is 8944 damage, which doesn't count the effect from my improved damage 3 item, which could be a potential 1700 more damage. <br>
<br>
On our end, there is mana management. As in, judge which mobs might be a good one to sit out and say, Medding through. If the rest of the group can handle one mob, then medding through one mob out of 5 is agreat way to not slow down the group. <br>
<br>
I would really like to see wizards get some upgrades, with all the upgrades other classes are getting. Some of our spells lines are useless, outdated or made obsolet with PoP. But we are group friendly, we do have something to offer groups, damage, it's what a wizard is about. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalrenfieryblade>Dalren Fieryblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/03 4:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Mages and Necromancers have to be nerfed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
