<br>
Pure DPS based on mana is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>NOT</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> group friendly unless it's a huge margin above what others contribute.  In the case of showing damage, this may actually work against wizards in the 50s as you will see Wizards hitting for 600-700ish, and mages hitting over 800 all the time, plus they have their pet and damage sheilds.  We can hit for 1200, but Ice Comet is not nearly as mana efficient as a draught, and we do all know it.  For most grouping, mana efficency is the key, since mana regen is so poor in this game.<br>
<br>
Thus the need for a way to help the group, not just damage the mob.  This need not be in the form of a buff.  I bet if you took Haste and clarity away from chanters completely, they'd still get groups easily in any dungeon you care to name.  Since they have an entire expansion slated to come out that is totally dungeons, I believe you'll see enchanters re-affirming their place in the holy triumvarite.  This will be due to mez which is a grouping utility, but not a buff.<br>
<br>
