<br>
The other spell would increase spell damage by 15% while at the same time increase mana cost by 20%.  This would be useful on most raid fights where you need to kill something before it kills your raid, and the fight doesn't really last long enough for the Wizards to come close to using up all of their mana.<br>
<br>
<br>
After seeing some of the effects on PoTime items, there is some potential for some decent spells using those effects as well.  For example make a wizard buff that absorbs 50 spell damage and does not wear off whenever the &quot;rune&quot; takes damage.  It would in effect always lower spell damage by 50 as long as the buff is in effect.<br>
<br>
Second would be a self buff that increases evasion rate by a large sum.  Somewhere in the line of 15%-20%.  It can be roleplayed into being Planar Shift or something to where the Wizards body isn't fully in the plane of existence he is currently fighting on, thus making it harder for melee attacks to make contact with him/her. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~kosmos00/elysig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
