<br>
Your absorb damage shield spell is good to. Lately, it seems Sony's answer to making things easier for casters is to combine several spells into one spell. Why not do the same for our two kinds of shield spells? Average the mana cost and have the spell give AC, HP and absorb damage all in one. That way we only have to cast one spell. Hmmm maybe this isn't as good as when I first thought it.<br>
<br>
We can be a &quot;buffing&quot; class if some of our self buffs became group buffs later on. If the effects from the level 54 and up familar also benifited anyone grouped with you, they would get see invis (no need for anyone to cast it while grouped), +20 to all resists, +75 mana, +2 mana regen tick, and reduced fizzle rate. That's alot, and all wizards always have thier familar up. At level 60 it's even more.<br>
<br>
Something else that could be added to Familars, a sort of debuff for mobs. At say level 54, the familar also increased the resists modifier for all none lure spells by -10, at level 60 -15 and so on. <br>
<br>
